Name: Parkinson's disease 1
Definition: A late onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in mutation in the alpha-synuclein gene on chromosome 4q22.1.

Name: Parkinson's disease 8
Definition: A late onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the dardarin encoding gene on chromosome 12q12.

Name: Parkinson's disease 4
Definition: A late onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in heterozygous triplication of the alpha-synuclein gene on chromosome 4q22.

Name: Parkinson's disease 17
Definition: A late-onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in heterozygous mutation in the VPS35 gene on chromosome 16q13.

Name: Parkinson's disease 14
Definition: A late-onset Parkinson disease that has_material_basis_in homozygous mutation in the PLA2G6 gene on chromosome 22q13.

Name: Parkinson's disease 22
Definition: A late onset Parkinson's disease that has_material_basis_in autosomal dominant inheritance of heterozygous mutation in the coiled-coil-helix-coiled-coil-helix domain containing 2 gene on chromosome 7p11.2.

Name: Parkinson's disease 3
Definition: A late onset Parkinson's disease characterized by mean age of onset of 59 years and that has_material_basis_in mutation in a locus in the 2p13 chromosome region.

Name: Parkinson's disease 21
Definition: A late onset Parkinson's disease characterized by autosomal dominant inheritance and mean age of onset at 67 years.
